============================================================
  ECONOMICS
============================================================

Concept:    Game Theory
Category:   Economics
Definition: Study of strategic interactions between rational agents
Formula:    Nash equilibrium
Economist:  John Nash
Example:    OPEC cartel coordination; nuclear deterrence strategy

Concept:    Diminishing Returns
Category:   Microeconomics
Definition: More of one input eventually yields smaller output increases
Formula:    Marginal product falls
Economist:  Turgot/Marshall
Example:    More workers in fixed factory eventually get in each other's way

Concept:    Elasticity
Category:   Microeconomics
Definition: Responsiveness of demand to price change
Formula:    PED = %dQd / %dP
Economist:  Alfred Marshall
Example:    Gasoline demand inelastic; luxury goods elastic

============================================================
  ARTIFICIAL INTELLIGENCE & MACHINE LEARNING
============================================================

Concept:     Backpropagation
Category:    Training
Definition:  Computes gradients via chain rule through network layers
Year:        1986
Researchers: Rumelhart/Hinton
Applications:Training all neural networks
Related:     Gradient descent, automatic differentiation

Concept:     Reinforcement Learning
Category:    Paradigm
Definition:  Agent learns from environment interaction to maximize reward
Year:        1950
Researchers: Bellman; Sutton/Barto
Applications:Games, robotics, recommendations, LLM alignment
Related:     Reward, policy, value function, Q-learning

Concept:     Attention Mechanism
Category:    Mechanism
Definition:  Learns to focus on relevant input parts for each output
Year:        2015
Researchers: Bahdanau et al.
Applications:Machine translation, NLP, summarization
Related:     Self-attention, multi-head, cross-attention

